With a final, convulsive motion, Cody leapt into the room, weapon poised for battle. He remained in that position for several
seconds, eyes darting about the room. He finally eased up, taking a relaxed stance, only to immediately return to the same
readied posture. When the attack stubbornly failed to materialize yet again, he finally relaxed in truth, rubbing his neck
self-consciously. "Stupid empty room," he muttered. "Would have fooled anyone."
